Oh huh, Agent Green. That's kind of interesting, I guess.

This work is really insubstantial2, but it feels like its all obscured in favor of a payoff that never comes. The object itself is fairly humdrum; it is a killbot made of nitrogen. Potentially interesting questions, such as who made it, why its made of nitrogen, what purpose it's supposed to serve, etc. are addressed, as far as I can tell, in the article.

The bulk of the article is Agent Green's account of initial containment, which fails to give any meaningful characterization, new information, or even particularly striking images. At the end, I was left waiting for a last-line reveal of  but nothing ever happened. Maybe the tale adds some wonderful context that makes reading this worthwhile, but a mainlist article should be able to stand on its own. -1

